-(ii), (c)-(iii)","option_b":"(a)-(ii), (b)-(iii), (c)-(i)","option_c":"(a)-(iii), (b)-(ii), (c)-(i)","option_d":"(a)-(iii), (b)-(i), (c)-(ii)","option_a_hi":"(a)-(i), (b)-(ii), (c)-(iii)","option_b_hi":"(a)-(ii), (b)-(iii), (c)-(i)","option_c_hi":"(a)-(iii), (b)-(ii), (c)-(i)","option_d_hi":"(a)-(iii), (b)-(i), (c)-(ii)"},{"id":708,"quiz_id":54,"topic_id":1011,"sort_order":3,"question":"Consider the following statements regarding the 'Iqta' system in the Delhi Sultanate:\\n\\n1. It was a system where land revenue assignments were given to nobles and military commanders instead of cash salaries.\\n\\n2. The holder of an Iqta was known as a Muqti or Wali.\\n\\n3. From the very beginning under Iltutmish, the Iqta system was strictly hereditary in nature.\\n\\nWhich of the statements given above is/are correct?","question_hi":"दिल्ली सल्तनत में 'इक्ता' प्रणाली के संबंध में निम्नलिखित कथनों पर विचार करें:\\n\\n1. यह एक ऐसी प्रणाली थी जिसमें नकद वेतन के बजाय अमीरों और सैन्य कमांडरों को भूमि राजस्व आवंटन दिया जाता था।\\n\\n2. इक्ता के धारक को मुक्ती या वली के नाम से जाना जाता था。\\n\\n3. इल्तुतमिश के अधीन शुरुआत से ही, इक्ता प्रणाली प्रकृति में सख्ती से वंशानुगत थी।\\n\\nऊपर दिए गए कथनों में से कौन-सा/से सही है/हैं?","option_a":"1 and 2 only","option_b":"1 and 3 only","option_c":"2 and 3 only","option_d":"1, 2, and 3","option_a_hi":"केवल 1 और 2","option_b_hi":"केवल 1 और 3","option_c_hi":"केवल 2 और 3","option_d_hi":"1, 2 और 3"},{"id":709,"quiz_id":54,"topic_id":1011,"sort_order":4,"question":"In the administrative machinery of the Delhi Sultanate, what was the primary responsibility of the 'Barid-i-Mumalik'?","question_hi":"दिल्ली सल्तनत के प्रशासनिक तंत्र में, 'बरीद-ए-मुमालिक' की प्राथमिक जिम्मेदारी क्या थी?","option_a":"Head of the royal bodyguards","option_b":"Head of the intelligence and postal department","option_c":"Chief Justice of the empire","option_d":"Superintendent of royal workshops (Karkhanas)","option_a_hi":"शाही अंगरक्षकों का प्रमुख","option_b_hi":"खुफिया और डाक विभाग का प्रमुख","option_c_hi":"साम्राज्य का मुख्य न्यायाधीश","option_d_hi":"शाही कारखानों का अधीक्षक"},{"id":710,"quiz_id":54,"topic_id":1011,"sort_order":5,"question":"Assertion (A): Sultan Firoz Shah Tughlaq made the Iqta assignments hereditary.\\n\\nReason (R): He wanted to assert strict central control and weaken the power of the provincial nobility.\\n\\nCodes:","question_hi":"अभिकथन (A): सुल्तान फ़िरोज़ शाह तुगलक ने इक्ता आवंटन को वंशानुगत बना दिया।\\n\\nकारण (R): वह सख्त केंद्रीय नियंत्रण स्थापित करना और प्रांतीय अमीरों की शक्ति को कमजोर करना चाहता था।\\n\\nकूट:","option_a":"Both A and R are true and R is the correct explanation of A","option_b":"Both A and R are true but R is not the correct explanation of A","option_c":"A is true but R is false","option_d":"A is false but R is true","option_a_hi":"A और R दोनों सत्य हैं और R, A का सही स्पष्टीकरण है","option_b_hi":"A और R दोनों सत्य हैं लेकिन R, A का सही स्पष्टीकरण नहीं है","option_c_hi":"A सत्य है लेकिन R असत्य है","option_d_hi":"A असत्य है लेकिन R सत्य है"},{"id":711,"quiz_id":54,"topic_id":1011,"sort_order":6,"question":"Which of the following statements regarding the 'Ariz-i-Mumalik' (Head of the Military Department) in the Delhi Sultanate is NOT correct?","question_hi":"दिल्ली सल्तनत में 'आरिज़-ए-मुमालिक' (सैन्य विभाग के प्रमुख) के संबंध में निम्नलिखित में से कौन सा कथन सही नहीं है?","option_a":"He acted as the supreme commander-in-chief of the army on the battlefield.","option_b":"He was responsible for the recruitment of soldiers.","option_c":"He maintained the descriptive roll of horses and soldiers.","option_d":"He was responsible for the payment of wages to the army.","option_a_hi":"उसने युद्ध के मैदान में सेना के सर्वोच्च कमांडर-इन-चीफ के रूप में कार्य किया।","option_b_hi":"वह सैनिकों की भर्ती के लिए जिम्मेदार था।","option_c_hi":"उसने घोड़ों और सैनिकों का वर्णनात्मक रोल बनाए रखा।","option_d_hi":"वह सेना को वेतन के भुगतान के लिए जिम्मेदार था।"},{"id":712,"quiz_id":54,"topic_id":1011,"sort_order":7,"question":"Consider the following statements regarding the local administration of the Delhi Sultanate:\\n\\n1. The provinces were divided into 'Shiqs', which were governed by Shiqdars.\\n\\n2. The 'Pargana' was a group of villages headed by an administrative officer called Amil.\\n\\n3. 'Khuts' and 'Muqaddams' were the chief administrative officials at the provincial level.\\n\\nWhich of the statements given above is/are correct?","question_hi":"दिल्ली सल्तनत के स्थानीय प्रशासन के संबंध में निम्नलिखित कथनों पर विचार करें:\\n\\n1. प्रांतों को 'शिक' में विभाजित किया गया था, जिन पर शिकदार शासन करते थे।\\n\\n2. 'परगना' गांवों का एक समूह था जिसका प्रमुख आमिल नामक प्रशासनिक अधिकारी होता था।\\n\\n3. 'खुत' और 'मुकद्दम' प्रांतीय स्तर पर मुख्य प्रशासनिक अधिकारी थे।\\n\\nऊपर दिए गए कथनों में से कौन-सा/से सही है/हैं?","option_a":"1 and 2 only","option_b":"2 and 3 only","option_c":"1 and 3 only","option_d":"1, 2, and 3","option_a_hi":"केवल 1 और 2","option_b_hi":"केवल 2 और 3","option_c_hi":"केवल 1 और 3","option_d_hi":"1, 2 और 3"},{"id":713,"quiz_id":54,"topic_id":1011,"sort_order":8,"question":"In the agrarian system of the Delhi Sultanate, the term 'Khalsa' specifically referred to:","question_hi":"दिल्ली सल्तनत की कृषि प्रणाली में, 'खालसा' शब्द विशेष रूप से संदर्भित करता है:","option_a":"Land assigned to religious and charitable institutions","option_b":"Crown land whose revenue was reserved directly for the Sultan's treasury","option_c":"Land granted to nobles as military assignments","option_d":"Barren land brought under cultivation by the state","option_a_hi":"धार्मिक और धर्मार्थ संस्थानों को सौंपी गई भूमि","option_b_hi":"मुकुट भूमि (शाही भूमि) जिसका राजस्व सीधे सुल्तान के खजाने के लिए आरक्षित था","option_c_hi":"सैन्य असाइनमेंट के रूप में अमीरों को दी गई भूमि","option_d_hi":"राज्य द्वारा खेती के अधीन लाई गई बंजर भूमि"},{"id":714,"quiz_id":54,"topic_id":1011,"sort_order":9,"question":"The official titled 'Amir-i-Akhur' during the Delhi Sultanate was the superintendent of the:","question_hi":"दिल्ली सल्तनत के दौरान 'अमीर-ए-आखूर' नामक अधिकारी किसका अधीक्षक था?","option_a":"Royal Kitchen","option_b":"Royal Stables","option_c":"Royal Elephants","option_d":"Royal Slaves","option_a_hi":"शाही रसोई","option_b_hi":"शाही अश्वशाला (अस्तबल)","option_c_hi":"शाही हाथी","option_d_hi":"शाही गुलाम"},{"id":715,"quiz_id":54,"topic_id":1011,"sort_order":10,"question":"Match the following army-related terms of the Delhi Sultanate with their correct meanings:\\n\\nList-I\\n(a) Hasham-i-Qalb\\n(b) Hasham-i-Atraf\\n(c) Daag\\n\\nList-II\\n(i) Branding of horses\\n(ii) Provincial Army\\n(iii) Royal Army at the center\\n\\nCodes:","question_hi":"दिल्ली सल्तनत के निम्नलिखित सेना-संबंधित शब्दों को उनके सही अर्थों के साथ सुमेलित करें:\\n\\nसूची-I\\n(a) हशम-ए-कल्ब\\n(b) हशम-ए-अतराफ\\n(c) दाग\\n\\nसूची-II\\n(i) घोड़ों को दागना\\n(ii) प्रांतीय सेना\\n(iii) केंद्र में शाही सेना\\n\\nकूट:","option_a":"(a)-(i), (b)-(ii), (c)-(iii)","option_b":"(a)-(ii), (b)-(iii), (c)-(i)","option_c":"(a)-(iii), (b)-(ii), (c)-(i)","option_d":"(a)-(iii), (b)-(i), (c)-(ii)","option_a_hi":"(a)-(i), (b)-(ii), (c)-(iii)","option_b_hi":"(a)-(ii), (b)-(iii), (c)-(i)","option_c_hi":"(a)-(iii), (b)-(ii), (c)-(i)","option_d_hi":"(a)-(iii), (b)-(i), (c)-(ii)"}]}